ibis.ipl.impl

Class Ibis

  • java.lang.Object
    • ibis.ipl.impl.Ibis
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ibis.ipl.Ibis, ibis.ipl.Manageable

    public abstract class Ibis
extends java.lang.Object
implements ibis.ipl.Ibis
    This implementation of the Ibis interface is a base class, to be extended by specific Ibis implementations.

      • doCreateReceivePort

        protected abstract ibis.ipl.ReceivePort doCreateReceivePort(ibis.ipl.PortType tp,
                                                            java.lang.String name,
                                                            ibis.ipl.MessageUpcall u,
                                                            ibis.ipl.ReceivePortConnectUpcall cU,
                                                            java.util.Properties properties)
                                                     throws java.io.IOException
        Creates a named ReceivePort of the specified port type, with upcall based communication. New connections will not be accepted until ReceivePort.enableConnections() is invoked. This is done to avoid upcalls during initialization. When a new connection request arrives, or when a connection is lost, a ConnectUpcall is performed.
        Parameters:
        tp - the port type.
        name - the name of this receiveport.
        u - the upcall handler.
        cU - object implementing gotConnection() and lostConnection() upcalls.
        properties - the port properties.
        Returns:
        the new receiveport.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - is thrown when the port could not be created.
